headline.main: ONE WEEK FROM CALIFORNIA.; ARRIVAL OF THE NORTH STAR. $1,239,209 IN SPECIE. THE PANAMA RAILROAD COMPLETED. LOS ANGELES EXCITEMENT. THE PORT OF MANZANILLA. THE COCOS ISLAND TREASURE. LATER FROM OREGON. LATER FROM THE SANDWICH ISLANDS. How the New King, Liholiho, Bears his Honors, EXTRACTS FROM AUSTRALIAN FILES. MARRIAGES, DEATHS, MARKETS, &c.

docs.lead_paragraph: The North Star rounded the Hook yesterday noon, and in spite of the terrible snow storm, came up to port before night. To purser Hull we are indebted for the early delivery of our packages, and for the following Memoranda. The Panama Railroad is at length completed. On the 28th ult. the train passed over the road from Aspinwall to Panama for the first time. val

headline.main: DICK TINTO ON HIS TRAVELS; A Ball at the Palace--The Grand Duke--The Heir who was not sent to bed before the party was over--The Wit of the Occasion--Italian Opera at Home, &c., &c.

docs.lead_paragraph: The festivities of Florentine fashion for the Winter were inaugurated on New-Year's evening, by a ball at the Palace. This building, as you know, is of historical note, having been founded early in the fifteenth century, by the vaunting LUCA PITTI, the opponent and rival of the MEDICI.

headline.main: NEW-YORK CITY.; Anti-Slavery Lecture, by Ralph Walde Emerson. Morrisania Railroad Meeting. Fire Department Commitee. The Hard-Shells. Mayor's Black Book. COMMON COUNCIL PROCEEDINGS. Board of Councilmen. Board of Education. THE AFRICAN SLAVE-TRADE. Charge of Fiting Out a Slaver.

docs.lead_paragraph: On Tuesday evening, at the Broadway Tabernacle, RALPH WALDO EMERSON delivered the eleventh of the course of Anti-Slavery Lectures before the New-York Anti-Slavery Society. There was a good attendance.
